# Knotwork — the lead, rebuilt to escape BRASS. The brass trap I kept
# falling into: saw + a filter envelope that opens on the attack IS the
# synth-brass recipe (the "waaah" swell). So: NO filter envelope sweep
# (filter_env 0 — the cutoff sits still, no attack bloom), and NO saw.
# The identity is instead AUDIBLE PWM: a pulse whose width sweeps hard
# and continuously (lfo_pwm 0.42), which is the most unmistakably
# electronic sound there is — no acoustic instrument's timbre morphs
# like that. A slow filter LFO adds a lazy auto-wah wobble on top.
# unison 3 detuned 16 cents makes three hollow pulses phase against
# each other. Slowish attack so there's no bright transient to read as
# a horn. Dark, hollow, wobbling, thick — a synthesizer, full stop.
unison 3
unison_detune 16
waveform 1
pulse_width 0.5
osc2_wave 1
osc2_pitch 0
osc2_level 0.6
osc3_wave 0
osc3_pitch 0
osc3_level 0
detune 5
sub 0.12
circuit 0
key_track 0.35
osc_fm 0
sync 0
ring 0
glide 0
attack 0.035
decay 0.5
sustain 0.85
release 0.45
filter_env 0.0
filter_attack 0.2
filter_decay 0.5
filter_sustain 0.5
filter_release 0.4
cutoff 1300
resonance 0.35
drive 1.3
saturation 1.0
hpf 80
volume 0.5
octave 4
noise 0
fuzz 0
spring 0.1
lfo_rate 0.35
lfo_shape 0.5
lfo_pitch 0
lfo_filter 0.22
lfo_pwm 0.42
